    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ab415e2d_a951ba2a",
        "filename": "util/misc/metrics.h",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 72,
      "author": {
        "id": 1144260
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-09-19T17:25:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hmm, just checked at https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/src/base/metrics/histogram_base.h?sq\u003dpackage:chromium\u0026dr\u003dCSs\u0026rcl\u003d1474269533\u0026l\u003d88 it\u0027s actually int32_t. Do you know what the right thing to do for \u003e 0x7fffffff is Will?",
      "parentUuid": "30695fe5_5d1e0b20",
      "revId": "07da507b2466afb52a00804d196f57eba59bf126",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ab415e2d_a9b29a4f",
        "filename": "util/misc/metrics.h",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 72,
      "author": {
        "id": 1160859
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-09-19T17:33:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "exception_code is DWORD, I think? I would leave that as a DWORD right up until you log the histogram, then do a cast to int32_t to actually log it.\n\nThe histograms.xml file already takes this into account and has a load of negative values in the enum for the high error codes. It\u0027s a bit hacky but that\u0027s what is done everywhere else.",
      "parentUuid": "ab415e2d_a951ba2a",
      "revId": "07da507b2466afb52a00804d196f57eba59bf126",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ab415e2d_1ca12a9b",
        "filename": "util/misc/metrics.h",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 72,
      "author": {
        "id": 1144260
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-09-19T17:44:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "OK, it looks like it\u0027s int on Mac https://developer.apple.com/reference/kernel/exception_type_t?language\u003dobjc.\n\nUm... I guess I\u0027ll do uint32_t in the helper method and then cast on calling UMA_*.",
      "parentUuid": "ab415e2d_a9b29a4f",
      "revId": "07da507b2466afb52a00804d196f57eba59bf126",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ab415e2d_7c406e38",
        "filename": "util/misc/metrics.h",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 72,
      "author": {
        "id": 1160859
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-09-19T18:14:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Sorry I did not realize this was used for both mac and win? If these codes are completely different meanings for each platform then the histogram should probably be different, since ideally the histograms.xml should point to an enum of the correct codes for that platform.\n\nI suggest having a Crashpad.ExceptionCode.Win or something like that, and another one for Mac - then when you add them to histograms you can point them at the right enum...?",
      "parentUuid": "ab415e2d_1ca12a9b",
      "revId": "07da507b2466afb52a00804d196f57eba59bf126",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
